\b \cf0 Semi-automated biography\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\qj\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 Inspired by the aforementioned reports produced by robot journalists, we tried to see what a biography based on RDF triples would look like. In order to create this biography, we have synthesized the information contained in the RDF triples collected by Alex. For the sake of clarity, we present in Figure 3 a simplified version, based only on Wikidata and three different versions of DBpedia (EN, FR, NL). This means that this experimental biography does not contain the list of books that Carton de Wiart wrote or on which he collaborated; apart from that, the content was redundant. \
\
As you can see (Figure 3), all the text fits in less than 20 lines. The result is far from Carton de Wiart's biography displayed by the State Archives of Belgium, let alone the 8-pages Biographical note in the National Biography. This confirms our first hypothesis: the overwhelming number of triples are redundant. Most triples express the same elements and often only offer basic information such as birth and death dates. In order to analyse the quality of this biography made up of disparate elements, we have highlighted the most problematic excerpts. The text in yellow points up contradictions. Firstly, it is not easy to know how to write the first name Henry. The spelling changes according to the language. In Wikidata, the first name is written with a \'ab\'a0Y\'a0\'bb at the end, whereas DBpedia uses an \'ab\'a0I\'a0\'bb. Secondly, DBpedia NL expresses that Carton de Wiart was a member of the \'ab\'a0cdH\'a0\'bb party  - which is erroneous and strictly impossible, since this poltiical party has been created after his death -, contrary to most knowledge bases which correctly indicate that Wiart belonged to the Catholic party.\
\
Moreover, the information is not always as structured and clear as we could imagine. For example, much of the information in DBpedia or Yago is not fully explicit. Thus, the Dutch version of DBpedia signals that Carton de Wiart belongs to the Wikipedia list "List of Belgian ministers of Justice". However, this piece of information would not be fully exploitable by a robot, not to mention the fact that the years of his tenure as Minister of Justice are not even indicated. Furthermore, it has to be noted that the properties used by Yago or DBpedia are often poorly defined or not defined at all. It is therefore difficult to ascertain what the "successor" property (highlighted in green in Figure 3) covers. Successor of who? At which position? \
