enriching the pre-existing vocabularies, such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://schema.org/Person"}}{\fldrslt http://schema.org/Person}}\
\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 secondly, \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
creating new linked open vocabularies. We can think about the Records in Context Ontology initiative, for example.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 - One alternative would be the injection of data directly in Wikidata. \
In that case, the institution could suggest the addition of new properties and take part in ongoing discussions.\
